import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    chart = sns.barplot(x='origin_destination', y='count', data=data)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        chart.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    plt.title("What is the most popular route?", wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()

import pandas as pd
import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    destination_counts = data.groupby('destination')['count'].sum().reset_index()
    destination_counts = destination_counts.sort_values('count', ascending=False)
    plt.pie(destination_counts['count'], labels=destination_counts['destination'], autopct='%1.1f%%')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of flights by destination?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
chart.show()
